President Obama releases a statement on the passing of Arlen Specter, highlighting his fighting spirit and dedication to serving the people. Specter's career as a prosecutor and senator was marked by his independence and commitment to putting the needs of the people first. Despite his personal struggles with cancer, Specter remained resilient and used his own story to inspire others. The President acknowledges Specter's efforts in advocating for stem-cell research funding and veterans' health, among other issues. President Obama extends his condolences to Specter's family.